trans-unit.source: DIOT requires all reported operations with vendors to have a type. In this step, you can set up a default value that all new vendors will get upon creation. If you specify this value with the wizard now, all vendors in your database will be updated with the value. Note that vendors that do not operate in Mexico cannot have the Lease and Rent operation type. Do not select Lease and Rent unless all the vendors you work with operate in Mexico.
trans-unit.note: Page DIOT Setup Wizard - Control DIOTOperationTypeDescription - Property InstructionalText

trans-unit.source: Set up default DIOT Type of Operation
trans-unit.note: Page DIOT Setup Wizard - Control DIOTOperationTypeDescription - Property Caption

trans-unit.source: DIOT requires all reported operations with vendors to have a type. In this step, you can set up a type for each vendor individually. This value will be used for all operations with the vendor, unless you specifically set another value in the individual document when posting. Currently, all vendors have a DIOT operation type equal to the default value that you selected in the previous step. If you do not want to change any existing vendors, you can ignore this step.

trans-unit.source: DIOT uses several concept definitions to provide VAT-related information to SAT. You must link your existing or future VAT posting setups to the appropriate concepts for this report to produce correct and valid numbers. Please set the links up on the DIOT Concept Links page.

Page DIOT Setup Wizard - Control DIOTConceptDescription - Property Caption

trans-unit.source: The DIOT is a monthly/quarterly declaration that is required by Mexican SAT. This extension will export your data to a properly formatted file that you can import into the government-provided tool. This wizard will guide you through setting up DIOT for the Mexico version of Dynamics 365 Business Central. If you do not want to set this up right now, close this page.
